ilog.cplex

Class IloCplex.Deserializer

  • java.lang.Object
    • ilog.cplex.IloCplex.Deserializer
  • Enclosing class:
    IloCplex

    public static class IloCplex.Deserializer
extends java.lang.Object
    A de-serializer for remote object user functions.

    Instances of this class de-serialize primitive types (byte, short, int, long, float, double) from an array of bytes. The assumptions this class makes about serialized data are compatible with the low-level serializers and de-serializer that the Callable Library (C API) routines CPXXserializercreate() and CPXXdeserializercreate() create. The assumptions are are also compatible with the serialized data created by IloCplex.Serializer.

    Proper serialization and de-serialization are required whenever data passes to or is returned from a user function because that function may run on a platform (combination of hardware and software) that represents low-level data differently.

    See Also:
    IloCplex.Serializer

      • IloCplex.Deserializer

        public IloCplex.Deserializer(int size,
                     byte[] data)
        Creates a new de-serializer that de-serializes data from an array of bytes.

        The constructor does not create a deep copy of data. Consequently, this array should not be changed at any time during the lifetime of the newly created instance.

        Parameters:
        size -

        Number of valid bytes in data.

        data - Serialized data.
